<title>USA: Goodyear Tire raises stake in India unit.</title>
<headline>Goodyear Tire raises stake in India unit.</headline>
<dateline>AKRON, Ohio 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Goodyear Tire &amp; Rubber Co said Thursday that the Reserve Bank of India had approved issuing additional shares to the company to increase ownership interest in its Goodyear India subsidiary.</p>
<p>Shareholders approved a $20 million capital increase on April 11 to be underwritten by Goodyear, increasing the company's majority ownership from 60 to 74 percent, the company said.</p>
<p>The capital increase, which required approval by 75 percent of the shareholders present, will be used for debt reduction, capital expenditures and expansion plans.</p>
<p>Goodyear said its Indian unit's net sales in 1997 are expected to be $130 million.</p>
